@startuml DailyRobotClassification_SP_AIRobotDetection
title CTS_DC_RobotDetection_GetLatest - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam activityBorderColor #4CAF50

start

:Stored Procedure Called;
note right
  **SP Name**: CTS_DC_RobotDetection_GetLatest
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsService (MySQL)
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
  **Called From**: RobotDetectionGetLatestCriteria
end note

partition "Input Parameters" {
  :Receive @ip_RobotDetectionLastID (long);
  note right
    **Last Processed ID**:
    - For incremental pagination
    - Start from last processed RobotDetectionID
    - WHERE RobotDetectionID > @ip_RobotDetectionLastID
  end note
}

partition "Get Pagination State" {
  :Read System Parameter (optional);
  note right
    **Already provided as input**:
    - @ip_RobotDetectionLastID from system parameter
    - No need to query again
    
    **Initial State** (first run):
    - @ip_RobotDetectionLastID = 0
    - Get all robots from beginning
    
    **Subsequent Runs**:
    - Start from last processed ID + 1
    - Incremental processing
  end note
}

partition "Query AI Robot Detections" {
  :Calculate batch size;
  note right
    **Batch Limit**: Configurable
    - Typical: 5000-10000 robots
    - Prevents memory overflow
    - Balance throughput vs resources
  end note

  :SELECT from RobotDetection table;
  note right
    **Query**:
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      RobotDetectionID,
      CustID,
      CategoryID,
      LastModifiedDate
    FROM RobotDetection
    WHERE RobotDetectionID > @ip_RobotDetectionLastID
    ORDER BY RobotDetectionID ASC
    LIMIT @batchSize
    ```
    
    **Filter Conditions**:
    1. **RobotDetectionID > @ip_RobotDetectionLastID**:
       - Incremental pagination
       - Skip already processed robots
       - Start from last + 1
    
    **Ordering**:
    - ORDER BY RobotDetectionID ASC
    - Consistent sequential processing
    - FIFO (First In, First Out)
    
    **Limit**:
    - Batch size for memory efficiency
    - Prevents overwhelming system
  end note
}

partition "Data Source Context" {
  note right
    **RobotDetection Table** (populated by AI/ML):
    
    **Table Structure**:
    ```sql
    CREATE TABLE RobotDetection (
      RobotDetectionID BIGINT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
      CustID BIGINT NOT NULL,
      CategoryID INT,              -- Robot category
      DetectionScore DECIMAL(5,2), -- AI confidence score
      DetectionDate DATETIME,      -- When AI detected
      LastModifiedDate DATETIME,
      ModelVersion VARCHAR(50),    -- ML model version
      DetectionReason TEXT,        -- Why flagged as robot
      INDEX idx_RobotDetectionID (RobotDetectionID),
      INDEX idx_CustID (CustID),
      INDEX idx_DetectionDate (DetectionDate)
    )
    ```
    
    **Populated By**: AI/ML Robot Detection System
    
    **AI Detection Criteria**:
    1. **Automated Betting Patterns**:
       - High-frequency betting (> threshold)
       - Consistent time intervals (< 10 seconds)
       - Repetitive bet amounts
       - Predictable patterns
    
    2. **Behavioral Indicators**:
       - API-based betting (not web UI)
       - No human-like randomness
       - Instant bet placement
       - Multiple simultaneous bets
    
    3. **ML Model Scoring**:
       - Pattern recognition algorithms
       - Historical data analysis
       - Confidence score calculation
       - Threshold-based flagging
    
    4. **Detection Score**:
       - 0-100 scale (higher = more confident)
       - Threshold: e.g., > 80 = robot
       - Model confidence level
    
    **Population Process**:
    1. ML model runs periodically (e.g., every hour)
    2. Analyzes all customer betting patterns
    3. Calculates robot detection score
    4. Scores above threshold inserted into table
    5. Includes model metadata (version, reason)
  end note
}

partition "Build Result Set" {
  :Build RobotAIEntity[];
  note right
    **Result Structure**:
    - RobotDetectionID (long) - For pagination
    - CustID (long) - Customer identifier
    - CategoryID (int) - Robot category
    - LastModifiedDate (DateTime)
    
    **Usage**:
    - CustID for PA insertion
    - CategoryID for robot category
    - RobotDetectionID for pagination tracking
  end note
}

:Return RobotAIEntity[];
note right
  **Return Type**: List<RobotAIEntity>
  
  **Count**: 0 to @batchSize robots
  
  **Empty Result Indicates**:
  - All AI robots processed
  - No new robots detected since last run
  - Job can complete
  
  **Non-Empty Result**:
  - Process these robots as PA
  - Update LastID after processing
  - May have more in next run
end note

:Log Execution;
note right
  **Logging**:
  - Robot count returned
  - RobotDetectionID range
  - Query execution time
  - Any errors/warnings
end note

note right
  **Pagination Logic Summary**:
  
  **First Iteration**:
  - @ip_RobotDetectionLastID = 0
  - Get first batch (oldest robots)
  - Return robots with IDs 1-5000 (example)
  - Next LastID = 5000
  
  **Subsequent Iterations**:
  - @ip_RobotDetectionLastID = 5000 (from previous)
  - Get next batch (IDs > 5000)
  - Return robots with IDs 5001-10000
  - Next LastID = 10000
  
  **Last Iteration**:
  - Returns < @batchSize robots (partial batch)
  - Or returns 0 robots (all processed)
  - LastID updated to MAX(RobotDetectionID)
  
  **Advantages**:
  1. **Simple Pagination**: Just use auto-increment ID
  2. **No Duplicates**: RobotDetectionID > @LastID prevents re-processing
  3. **Fast Queries**: Index on RobotDetectionID
  4. **Resumable**: Can resume from LastID if interrupted
  5. **Consistent**: ORDER BY ensures reliable pagination
  
  **AI/ML Integration**:
  - This SP is **consumer** of AI/ML output
  - AI/ML system is **producer** (populates RobotDetection)
  - Decoupled architecture
  - ML model can evolve independently
  - Audit trail of AI detections preserved
  
  **Performance**:
  - Query time: < 500ms (with index)
  - Batch size: 5000-10000 (configurable)
  - Memory efficient
  - Scalable to millions of robots
  
  **Business Logic**:
  - Only AI-confirmed robots processed
  - ML model confidence baked in
  - Automatic classification (no manual review)
  - Continuous monitoring and detection
  
  **Comparison with TW Robot**:
  - AI Robot: Automated, ML-based, ID pagination
  - TW Robot: Rule-based, manual, time pagination
  - AI: Fast (300s), TW: Slow (900s)
  - AI: Simple, TW: Complex
end note

stop

@enduml

